almond extract makes cherries taste cheerier, add just a drop or two to cherry pies and other baked goods.
easy mushroom sauce, heat 1 cup beef broth, reduce to 1/4 cup, add 2 cups pureed canned cream of mushroom soup.
herbal salt sub, combine 2 tbs dried parsley, 1 tbs dried tarragon, 2 tsp each dried oregano and celery flakes.
leftover risotto, refridge it to use as a base for risotto pancakes.
chop sticky raisins, coat your knife blade with nonstick cooking spray.
easy access, prepare your fav bread pudding recipe in a muffin tin= individual the go dessert.
BBQ cheese popcorn, mix 3/4 tsp chili powder, 1/2 tsp garlic salt, 1/3 cup grated parm, toss with the warm fresh popcorn to coat.
kicked up apple pie, roll finely chopped crisp cooked bacon into your pie dough, form, fill, bake.
make crispier pickles, refridge the vegetables before pickling, cold produce makes crisp pickles.
kick up that chicken salad, add about 1/2 cup chopped roasted pecans into 6-8 cups of your fav chicken salad recipe.

quick artichoke pasta sauce, chop 1 jar marinated artichoke hearts, toss in their marinade, add 1 cup crumbled feta cheese with 3/4 lb pasta
in a hurry, use wonton skins or egg roll skins when making ravioli.
boost flavor in seafood paella, replace 1 cup of the chicken broth with 1 cup bottled clam juice.
jump start onions that are slow to caramelize, sprinkle them with a bit of brown sugar.
help fried meatballs brown without sticking or crumbling, dredge the meatballs with a little flour before frying.
add crunch to chicken salad, stir 1/2 cup or more of peeled, chopped Jicama into your fav chicken salad.
prevent drips in that ice cream cone, stuff a mini marshmallow in the bottom of a sugar cone.
Italian herb seasoning, 2 tbs each dried oregano, basil and 2 tsp dried thyme. makes about 1/4 cup.
kicked up grapefruit, halve the fruit, sprinkle with dash of honey, broil till golden.
Homemade ginger ale,1 cup sugar,1 cup water,1/3 cup sliced,unpeeled ginger,bring to boil, simmer 5 minutes,cool,discard ginger,add club soda

kicked up flavors, add sliced or grated ginger to lemonade, fruit juices, or your fav iced tea.
mute the frozen taste, thaw frozen fish in cold milk.
kicked up salads, sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped figs onto your fav mix of salad greens, pair with a citrus vinaigrette.
add rich flavor to mashed potatoes, use evaporated milk in place of 1/2 cup of the milk called for in the recipe.
kicked up frozen corn, brown it in a little bacon fat to allow the corn flavor to blossom.
kicked up coleslaw, add grated zest of 1 lemon,1-2 tbs lemon juice, 1/4 tsp celery seeds or 1/2 tsp celery salt to your fav coleslaw recipe.
easy chorizo chili,1/2 lb soft mexican chorizo,saute till crumbly,add 2 cans drained pinto beans and 1/2 cup tomato sauce,simmer 10 minutes.
keep a cut cake moist, place a cut apple in the storage container, its a science thing.
instant beet borscht, 1 jar pickled beets, wiz in blender, with 2 cups cold buttermilk, 1 cup ice water, 1/3 cup chopped fresh dill.
basic beer batter, 1 cup AP flour, 1/2 cup cornstarch, 11/2 cups beer, whisk, chill 1 hour before using.

quick dip for raw vegetables,beat together 1 cup each sour cream and cottage cheese,1 packet dried vegetable soup mix.
perk up spaghetti sauce, add 1 to 2 cups of vegetable juice to your fav spaghetti sauce when simmering.
kicked up polenta, replace 1-2 cups of the broth with vegetable juice.
kick up your fav soup recipe, replace 1/2 of the broth or water with vegetable juice.
kicked up tuna salad, use a combo of solid white and chunk light tuna in your recipe.
